From: 3090 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-04
Subject: [PATCH] gemma4_mm: process video frames one-at-a-time in get_video_feature

Closes Gemma 4 video OOM on Ampere AND R9700's bsz==1 vision-attention
assertion in one shot. The batched vt(pv, pp) call materializes a
[num_frames x num_patches x 2 x position_embedding_size] one_hot tensor
inside Gemma4VisionPatchEmbedder._position_embeddings (~1.24 GB bf16 for
a 12-frame video at pooling_kernel_size=3 / 10240 classes) — OOMs after
LM weights + KV pool. Per-frame calls keep the peak at 1/num_frames and
satisfy the RDNA4 bsz==1 assertion. Validated 2026-05-04 (4/4 PASS).

Regenerated 2026-06-10 with wide context: the original hand-written hunk
had no unique anchor, so on an already-patched tree git apply matched the
get_image_feature block (same vt(pv, pp) shape) and would silently patch
the IMAGE path on a setup.sh rerun. Context now pins the video-only
4D->3D reshape so re-application fails cleanly. Narrative:
patches/README.md.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py b/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py
index 40e06f647..615b7198a 100644
--- a/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py
@@ -466,24 +466,40 @@ class Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration(PreTrainedModel):
                 # 3-D (num_frames, num_patches, ...) so each frame is a
                 # batch element for the vision tower.
                 if pv.dim() == 4:
                     pv = pv.reshape(-1, pv.shape[-2], pv.shape[-1])
                 if pp.dim() == 4:
                     pp = pp.reshape(-1, pp.shape[-2], pp.shape[-1])
 
                 pv = pv.to(device=vt.device, dtype=self.language_model.dtype())
                 pp = pp.to(device=vt.device)
 
-                pooled, pooler_mask = vt(pv, pp)
-
-                for hs, mask in zip(pooled, pooler_mask):
-                    real_tokens = hs[mask]
+                # Process frames one-at-a-time instead of as a single batch.
+                # The batched call (pv shape [num_frames, num_patches, ...])
+                # materializes a one_hot tensor of size num_frames *
+                # num_patches * 2 * position_embedding_size in
+                # Gemma4VisionPatchEmbedder._position_embeddings (~1.24 GB
+                # for 12 frames at pooling_kernel_size=3 / 10240 classes /
+                # bf16), which OOMs on Ampere TP=1 after the LM weights +
+                # KV pool are loaded. Per-frame keeps that allocation at
+                # 1/num_frames the size with the same total throughput
+                # cost (vt is the bottleneck either way at video time).
+                # Also avoids the bsz==1 assertion at attention/vision.py:
+                # 254 that the RDNA4 stack hit on the same model — single-
+                # batch calls satisfy both constraints. Validated 2026-05-04
+                # via gemma4 preset port 23355 — patch 026.
+                num_frames = pv.shape[0]
+                for f in range(num_frames):
+                    pooled_f, mask_f = vt(pv[f : f + 1], pp[f : f + 1])
+                    # pooled_f: [1, output_len, hidden]
+                    # mask_f:   [1, output_len]
+                    real_tokens = pooled_f[0][mask_f[0]]
                     all_embeds.append(
                         self.embed_vision(
                             inputs_embeds=real_tokens.unsqueeze(0)
                         ).squeeze(0)
                     )
 
         if all_embeds:
             return torch.cat(all_embeds, dim=0)
         else:
             return torch.empty(
